\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4}{\ignorespaces \textbf  {Joint-key conflict-resolution routing.} The retrieval key is formed from both surface-text semantic embeddings and hidden-state activation features. When the activation anomaly exceeds the routing threshold and conflicts with benign-looking surface semantics, lexicographic override suppresses the semantic branch and forces retrieval to use activation-driven safety exemplars from the golden dataset, preventing PBU-style camouflage from hijacking exemplar selection.}}{8}{figure.4}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:jointkey}{{4}{8}{\textbf {Joint-key conflict-resolution routing.} The retrieval key is formed from both surface-text semantic embeddings and hidden-state activation features. When the activation anomaly exceeds the routing threshold and conflicts with benign-looking surface semantics, lexicographic override suppresses the semantic branch and forces retrieval to use activation-driven safety exemplars from the golden dataset, preventing PBU-style camouflage from hijacking exemplar selection}{figure.4}{}}
